{"name": "ml-package-kavya", "metadata": {"name": "ml-package-kavya", "version": "0.0.1", "classifiers": [], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "ml_package installs the code required for predicting House price.", "upload_time": 1733549997}, "documentation": ["# Median housing value prediction\n\nThe housing data can be downloaded from https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ageron/handson-ml/master/. The script has codes to download the data. We have modelled the median house value on given housing data. \n\nThe following techniques have been used: \n\n - Linear regression\n - Decision Tree\n - Random Forest\n\n## Steps performed\n - We prepare and clean the data. We check and impute for missing values.\n - Features are generated and the variables are checked for correlation.\n - Multiple sampling techinuqies are evaluated. The data set is split into train and test.\n - All the above said modelling techniques are tried and evaluated. The final metric used to evaluate is mean squared error.\n\n## To excute the script\npython < scriptname.py >\n"], "modules": [{"name": "ml-package-kavya.nonstandardcode", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "ml-package-kavya.nonstandardcode.fetch_housing_data", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "housing_url", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "housing_path", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ml-package-kavya.nonstandardcode.load_housing_data", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "housing_path", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ml-package-kavya.nonstandardcode.income_cat_proportions", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "ml-package-kavya.nonstandardcode.DOWNLOAD_ROOT", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ml-package-kavya.nonstandardcode.